The course provides basic knowledge of complaints, patogenesis, algorithms of diagnostics and treatment as well as prevention of diseases of ear-nose-throat, head and neck . The course consists of academic lectures and practical training.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aim is to provide students basic knowledge in ear-nose-throat, head and neck anatomy, physiology, patology and functions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who gratuated the course: -is able to take clinical history and perform physical examination of the patient, including observation of otorhinolaryngological status -is able to evaluate and interpret main investigation methods in otorhinolaryngology (audiometry, tympanometry, radiological investigations of the head and neck region) -has an overview of the symptomatology, etiopathogenesis, diagnosis and management of common ear, nose, and throat diseases including head and neck region.
